At the Open R&amp;Day 2019 Conference in Paris, I gave a talk titled Our journey from Jenkins to Jenkins X.
In this talk, I first introduced Jenkins X, and then went through some of the benefits we gained by switching Dailymotion ad-tech platform&rsquo;s CI/CD pipelines to Jenkins X: Preview Environments, easy promotion, Gitops, &hellip;
I also explained how we adopted Jenkins X and did the migration, and finished with our open-source contributions as part of this migration.

Helm is a package manager for Kubernetes. It is the tool most people use to package their applications, and then deploy on Kubernetes. It is also the core of an ecosystem growing every day: plugins, wrapper tools, charts, &hellip;
I have been contributing to a few open-source projects in the Helm ecosystem:
Helmfile - a &ldquo;declarative spec for deploying helm charts&rdquo; Helm Unit Tests plugin - a plugin for running unit tests on Helm charts Helm Tiller plugin - a plugin for running Helm in &ldquo;tiller-less&rdquo; mode in Helm 2 Helm charts - various contributions to common charts I&rsquo;ve been using
